title: GPS-deduced 1-hour Total Electron Content (TEC) global maps and movies, UPC= U Politec. Catalonia Barcelona Spain, ESA= ESOC Darmstadt Germany (starting 20 Feb 2011)  - International Global Navigation Satellite Systems (GNSS) Service Ionosphere Working Group

info.contact: International Global Navigation Satellite Systems (GNSS) Service Ionosphere Working Group @

parameters.name: tecUHRM3
parameters.description: UPC, Rapid-TEC Global Maps, Total Electron Content (TEC) in TECU (10^16 m-2) - (Rapid product, 1 hr res., 24 hrs latency), Mapped Cylindrical Image. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['tecUHR']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
